					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13497623#post-4713613</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-13497623/scp-5581#post-4713613</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Wed, 08 Jul 2020 21:45:33 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>DarkStuff</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1581620</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>This made me smile. However:</p> <blockquote> <p>Following transfiguration, surviving subjects report being transported to an unknown location, SCP-5581-1.</p> </blockquote> <p>This makes it sound like they only <em>report</em> being transported, and actually remain in place. You should make it explicit that they suddenly disappear after the transformation, and reappear in the same place approximately [x] minutes/hours/days/whatever later. I was confused there for a second.</p> <p>Anyways, +1. I first thought of pool when you said &quot;large green rectangle&quot;, and then I thought of ping pong when I considered the divisor, and then it turned out to be tennis! And now the pun makes sense.</p> <p>Also, fantastic imagery for the transformation. I was actually able to follow it and visualize it.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
